From: MINORI IKEDA <daisysi9@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] tab: fix typo in zoom_font_scales array initializer

In the zoom_font_scales[] initializer, the last large-zoom entry reads:

    1.0 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1,2,

In a C array initializer the comma is the element separator, so "1,2"
is parsed as two separate elements: the value 1.0*1.2^6*1 (≈2.986) and
the literal 2. This gives the array 17 elements instead of the intended
16, making:
  - index 15 duplicate the value of index 14 (both ≈2.986 instead of ≈3.583)
  - an unreachable extra element 2.0 at index 16

Change "1,2" to "1.2" so the maximum zoom level is correctly 1.2^7 ≈ 3.583.

Fixes: https://gitlab.gnome.org/chergert/ptyxis/-/issues/XXXX
---
 src/ptyxis-tab.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/ptyxis-tab.c
+++ b/src/ptyxis-tab.c
@@ -137,7 +137,7 @@ static double zoom_font_scales[] = {
   1.0 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2,
   1.0 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2,
   1.0 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2,
-  1.0 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1,2,
+  1.0 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2 * 1.2,
 };
